//! Bevy-native, opinionated Figma-shaped document model ‚Äî the core
//! crate.
//!
//! This crate **defines components and the document taxonomy**.
//! It is intentionally domain-agnostic about *where* a scene came from
//! ‚Äî Figma import, hand-authored, generated by an agent, or
//! procedurally ‚Äî and serves as the test substrate for the
//! `kyoso_graph` infrastructure.
//!
//! For the Figma REST-API ‚Üí ECS import adapter, see the sibling
//! `kyoso_figma` crate.
//!
//! ## What this crate provides
//!
//! - **Component definitions** ‚Äî `Frame`, `Rectangle`, `Text` and their
//!   value-type satellites `Size`, `Paint`, `TypeStyle`. Each is a Bevy
//!   `Component` with `derive(SchemaSync)` so per-field mutations
//!   replicate via the `kyoso_sync` typed schema path. CRDT-kind choice
//!   per field (LWW for scalars, OrSet for fills, Sequence for collab
//!   text, nested for TypeStyle inside Text).
//! - **Structural markers** ‚Äî `SceneNode` and `SceneEdge` (zero-sized
//!   types) used as the `<N, E>` parameters to
//!   [`kyoso_graph_sync::GraphSyncPlugin`]. Every spawned scene entity
//!   carries `SceneNode` plus exactly one of the field-bearing components.
//! - **`KyosoCorePlugin`** ‚Äî single-call entry point that registers
//!   all per-component schema plugins.
//!
//! ## Opinionated departures from Figma's data model
//!
//! - **Group + Frame unified** as `Frame` with a `clips_content: bool`.
//! - **No `absolute_bounding_box`** ‚Äî position+rotation+scale via
//!   Bevy `Transform`; size via the standalone `Size` component.
//!   World coords come from `GlobalTransform` on demand.
//! - **Idiomatic Rust field names** ‚Äî snake_case; `is_clip` ‚Üí
//!   `clips_content`; etc.
//!
//! ## Initial cut scope
//!
//! Three node types: `Frame`, `Rectangle`, `Text`. `Page` /
//! `Component` / `Instance` / `Vector` / `Group` / `BooleanOperation`
//! and the rest of Figma's surface are deferred.

